# Git Workflow Standards

> **Related Rules**: See [Git-like Branching Model](./git-model.mdc), [Linting](./linting.mdc), [Code Quality](./code-quality.mdc)

## Conventional Commits

- All commit messages must follow Conventional Commits format
- Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore

## Husky Git Hooks

- Pre-commit hook runs linting and type checking
- Commit-msg hook validates commit message format
- Pre-push hook runs tests (optional)

## lint-staged Configuration

- Only lint modified files
- Auto-fix issues when possible
- Block commit if linting fails

## Branch Strategy

- Main branch: `main` or `master`
- Feature branches: `feature/<feature-name>`
- Bug fix branches: `fix/<bug-name>`
- Refactor branches: `refactor/<refactor-name>`

